# Fitness Metric Board

A modern web application tailored for gyms to efficiently manage member information, visualize activity data, facilitate check-ins, and provide instant answers to gym-specific queries through an integrated chatbot.

## Overview

Fitness Metric Board empowers gym staff and management with actionable insights and streamlined workflows:

- **Data Visualization:** Interactive dashboards display member stats, attendance patterns, and more.
- **Member Registration:** Quick and easy on-boarding for new gym members.
- **Member Check-in:** Digital check-in for members to track attendance and usage.
- **Gym Chatbot:** Built-in AI chatbot answers common questions, assists with onboarding, and provides information unique to your gym.

## Technology Stack

- **Frontend:** React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn-ui
- **Build Tooling:** Vite

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js and npm (see [nvm installation guide](https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm#installing-and-updating))

### Local Development

```sh
# Clone the repository
git clone <YOUR_GIT_URL>
cd fitness-metric-board

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Start the development server
npm run dev
```

### Editing Code

You can work on Fitness Metric Board using any of the following methods:

- **Lovable Platform:** Edit and deploy instantly at [Lovable Project](https://lovable.dev/projects/029d44f9-aeec-46c7-9710-af12a49611b2).
- **GitHub Web Editor:** Edit files directly in your browser.
- **GitHub Codespaces:** Launch a cloud-based development environment for instant coding and testing.

## Deployment

Easily publish your project via Lovable:

1. Go to [Lovable](https://lovable.dev/projects/029d44f9-aeec-46c7-9710-af12a49611b2).
2. Click Share → Publish.

## Custom Domains

To connect a custom domain:

1. Navigate to Project → Settings → Domains on Lovable.
2. Click "Connect Domain" and follow the prompts.

More details: [Custom Domain Guide](https://docs.lovable.dev/tips-tricks/custom-domain#step-by-step-guide)

